    "There is a growing interest in using deep learning techniques to enhance retrieval accuracy, even if it means sacrificing some level of comprehensibility.",
    "The dual encoder architecture is a common design for dense retrieval models.",
    "(Hambarde and Proenca, 2023) The system comprises of two distinct networks that receive separate inputs, namely queries and documents, and independently generate dense embeddings for each input.",
    "Due to its high accuracy and dual-encoder structure, which is more suitable for RALM, most articles choose to use the dense indexing method to build their retrievers.",
